<text id="03-failure-modes" title="Requirements Documentation Failure Modes" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>Antipatterns observed in real engagements applying requirements-documentation. Each entry pairs symptom + root cause + fix.</summary>

  <section title="Antipatterns">
    <antipattern id="solution-not-need" severity="high">
      <symptom>BR phrased as solution ('use Salesforce').</symptom>
      <root-cause source="BABOK v3 + field experience">Sponsor pre-decided.</root-cause>
      <fix>BR is the why; SR is the what. Reject solution-shaped BRs.</fix>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern id="single-source-citation" severity="high">
      <symptom>SR cites only one elicitation session.</symptom>
      <root-cause source="BABOK v3 + field experience">BA in a hurry.</root-cause>
      <fix>Require ≥2 source citations per record.</fix>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern id="missing-acceptance-criteria" severity="medium">
      <symptom>SR has no acceptance criteria.</symptom>
      <root-cause source="BABOK v3 + field experience">Author treats AC as optional.</root-cause>
      <fix>Block sign-off; AC is mandatory.</fix>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern id="inline-glossary-violation" severity="medium">
      <symptom>SR inline-defines a term instead of linking.</symptom>
      <root-cause source="BABOK v3 + field experience">Drift across docs.</root-cause>
      <fix>Replace inline definition with glossary link; PRD linter enforces.</fix>
    </antipattern>
  </section>
</text>
